info.title: PowerConnectApi
info.description:
Rich set of APIs that opens up PowerCARD to 3rd party systems to interact in real-time with any of the digital channels

  • Transacting and Servicing APIs available through more than 150+ web services
  • Online portal to access web services user guides and to test projects through the sand box

post.description: Approve Provisioning StandIn Notification Web WebService

Description.description: Human-readable short description of the reasonCode

Source.description: The application or component that generated this error.

Details.description: Optional detailed description provides information about data received and calculated during request processing.  This helps the user to diagnose errors.
Details.example: This is mandatory field while requesting for fraud submission.

ReasonCode.description: Reason code is a unique constant identifying the error case encountered during request processing.

Recoverable.description: Recoverable flag indicates whether this error is always returned for this request, or retrying could change the outcome.  For example, 'true' or 'false'.

Error.description: Errors array wrapped in an error object
Errors array wrapped in an error object

line1.description: Line 1 of the street address of the merchant. Usually includes the street number and name.

line2.description: Line 2 of the street address of the merchant. Usually includes the unit or suite number.

city.description: Name of the city or town where the merchant is located

postalCode.description: Postal code where the merchant is located

countryCode.description: Country code in ISO-3166-1 alpha 3 format (3 letters)

countrySubdivisionCode.description: State, province, or territory code in ISO 3166-2 format, second part (i.e., country code and hyphen excluded)

Address.description: Address of the merchant. This is currently in Beta and is available only in selected markets.

searchResults.description: List of Back Office Clarity API search results

recordId.description: Unique identifier of a transaction response.

BackOfficeSearchResult.description: List of Back Office Clarity API search results

url.description: URL to access the Ethoca-generated Call Center view for the specific transaction. Note that this link expires based on the expiresOn timestamp.

contentType.description: Designates the type of content expected in the call center, either Merchant and Transaction information (TRANSACTION_DETAILS) or enhanced merchant details (MERCHANT_DETAILS)

expiresOn.description: Timestamp when the Call Center Transaction expires in Coordinated Universal Time (UTC). ISO 8601 format

CallCenterDetails.description: Note that a call center URL is only returned in the response if you have added the Consumer Clarity Call Center service to your project.

carbonEmissionInGrams.description: The transaction's CO2 emission in grams.

carbonEmissionInOunces.description: The transaction's CO2 emission in ounces.

CarbonFootprint.description: Carbon score details calculated for specific transaction.

mainCategory.description: Main category to which an MCC belongs.

subCategory.description: Sub-category of a category to which an MCC belongs.

sector.description: Sector of a category to which an MCC belongs.

sectorCode.description: Unique code assigned to each sector.

cacheable.description: Indicates if the merchant data provided in the response can be cached.

cacheExpiry.description: Indicates the caching expiry date-time (in ISO 8601 format) if caching is permitted.

attribution.description: An URL indicating data attribution to third party data sources if applicable.

requiredMap.description: Indicates restriction on the Map to be used to display geolocation (latitude and longitude) details. No restriction or requirement if this field is null or not present.

DataPolicy.description: Indicates if the merchant data provided in the response includes regulations to be followed by the issuer.

name.description: Name of intermediary that facilitated the transaction.

logos.description: Returns logo details, if available, for the transaction intermediary of size 200 x 200 pixels.

Intermediary.description: Intermediary to identify how transaction was facilitated

url.description: Absolute URL to access the intermediary logo image.

altTextTag.description: Alt text tag for intermediary logos to provide for accessibility.

code.description: Merchant category code associated with the merchant category code for the merchant

description.description: Merchant category description associated with the merchant category code for the merchant

MerchantCategory.description: Merchant category code and description associated with the merchant.

latitude.description: Latitude coordinate where the purchase was made

longitude.description: Longitude coordinate where the purchase was made

type.description: Proximity type of map coordinates returned based on address available for the merchant

MerchantLocation.description: Information associated with the physical location of the purchase

url.description: Absolute URL to access the logo image.

type.description: Indicates if the logo belongs to a Merchant or an Industry. Possible values are: MERCHANT, INDUSTRY.

altTextTag.description: Alt text tag for logos to provide for accessibility.

description.description: Brief description of the merchants products and/or services. This is currently in Beta and is available only for selected merchants.
description.example: Provider of top quality shoe wear for men, women, and children.

websiteUrl.description: Website URL of the merchant. This is currently in Beta and is available only in selected markets.

logos.description: List of logos associated with the merchant or industry.

sensitiveContentTypes.description: This field indicates that a merchant might sell products and services containing the returned sensitive content type. However, it does not mean that all transactions under a merchant contain such content type. Not all merchants have a sensitive content type categorization, only those categorized will return that value today.

items.description: This field indicates that a merchant might sell products and services containing the returned sensitive content type. However, it does not mean that all transactions under a merchant contain such content type. Not all merchants have a sensitive content type categorization, only those categorized will return that value today.

url.description: URL to access the Ethoca-generated digital receipt for the specific transaction. Note that this link expires based on the expiresOn timestamp.

contentType.description: Designates the type of content expected in the purchase receipt, either purchase-level information (RECEIPT) or enhanced merchant details (MERCHANT_DETAILS)

expiresOn.description: Timestamp when the purchase receipt expires in Coordinated Universal Time (UTC). ISO 8601 format

PurchaseReceipt.description: Note that a purchase receipt URL is only returned in the response if you have added the Consumer Clarity Digital Receipt service to your project.

code.description: Machine-readable code explaining the status of the result, not a HTTP status code

message.description: Human-readable description explaining the status of the result, and guidance to resolve errors (if applicable), not a HTTP status message
message.example: OK. / Merchant results provided. / Purchase Receipt available.

cancellationStatusReasonCode.description: Describes the reason for the cancellation state. Supported values are COMPANY_NOT_RESPONDING, COMPANY_NOT_ACCEPTING, COMPANY_CANNOT_FIND_SUBSCRIPTION, USER_WRONG_INFORMATION_PROVIDED.

estimatedProcessingDays.description: Estimated processing days required to cancel subscription.

cancellationMethod.description: The method that was selected when the cancellation was initiated. Supported values are AUTOMATED | GUIDED.

recordId.description: Unique identifier of a transaction response.

ClarityShortSearchResult.description: List of Consumer Clarity API search results

searchResults.description: List of Consumer Clarity API search results

frequency.description: Frequency of a recurring transaction. Supported values are WEEKLY | BI_WEEKLY | MONTHLY | QUARTERLY | HALF_YEARLY | YEARLY.

type.description: The type of a recurring payment. Supported values are SUBSCRIPTION | OTHER_RECURRING_EXPENSE.

supportedCancellationMethods.description: Supported cancellation methods available for a recurring transaction. Supported values are AUTOMATED | GUIDED.

items.description: Supported cancellation methods available for a recurring transaction. Supported values are AUTOMATED | GUIDED.

yearlyAmount.description: Estimated yearly amount the cardholder is saving from cancelling a subscription.

RecurringPaymentKey.description: Identification lookup recurring payment key details.

subscriptionStatus.description: The state in which a recurring cancellation request is in. Supported values are INITIATED | IN_PROGRESS | COMPLETED | DENIED | ACTION_NEEDED. In case of ACTION_NEEDED, need to initiate with CANCEL-RETRY-DATA to perform subscription cancellation action.

createdDate.description: Indicates the date in which a recurring cancellation request was created.

updatedDate.description: Indicates the date in which a recurring cancellation request was last updated.

subscriptionStateId.description: Unique ID to track the status of a cancellation request.
